# EDAMAME Security - Public Issue Tracker & Documentation

> **Master Repository:** `edamame_app` - See `../edamame_app/.cursor/rules/workspace.mdc` for workspace-wide rules.

## Project Context
This repository is the public-facing issue tracker, documentation hub, and
screenshot gallery for EDAMAME Security. The app itself is closed source;
this repo holds:
- `README.md`, `AGENTIC.md`, `PLUGINS.md` -- user-facing documentation
- `features.json` -- feature metadata for the wiki generator
- `macos/`, `windows/`, `linux/`, `ios/`, `android/` -- platform screenshots
- `.github/workflows/feature-wiki.yml` -- CI that regenerates the GitHub wiki

## Screenshot History Hygiene (MUST follow on every push)

Automated screenshot commits (`chore: Update screenshots from edamame_app`)
accumulate rapidly and bloat the repo. Before pushing to the remote, squash
old screenshot commits so that **at most 4** of the most recent screenshot
commits survive as individual commits. Older screenshot history is collapsed
into the baseline.

### Procedure

1. Count screenshot commits: `git log --oneline | grep -c "chore: Update screenshots"`
2. If the count exceeds 4:
   a. Identify the 5th-oldest screenshot commit (the first one to squash into the baseline).
   b. Soft-reset to the parent of that commit, preserving the working tree.
   c. Re-commit the squashed range as a single commit:
      `Historical screenshots update` (or amend into the existing baseline commit).
   d. Cherry-pick or rebase the remaining recent commits (the 4 kept screenshot
      commits plus any non-screenshot commits on top).
   e. Force-push: `git push --force origin main`
   f. Delete stale remote tags, re-tag the new HEAD, push tags.
3. If the count is 4 or fewer, push normally.

**Why force-push is safe here:** This repo has no external contributors or
branch protection. The only automated committer is the screenshot CI workflow.

### Quick one-liner check before push
```bash
SC=$(git log --oneline | grep -c "chore: Update screenshots"); echo "$SC screenshot commits"; [ "$SC" -gt 4 ] && echo "SQUASH NEEDED before push"
```

## Tags

Tags follow `vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH` and are set by the release workflow in
`edamame_app`. After a history rewrite (squash), delete old tags and re-tag
HEAD:

```bash
git tag -l | xargs git tag -d
git push origin --delete $(git ls-remote --tags origin | awk '{print $2}' | sed 's|refs/tags/||')
git tag vX.Y.Z
git push origin vX.Y.Z
```

